on civilization. Billions have perished  

99
00:08:37,200 --> 00:08:42,480
while an egg-shaped moon is still drawing 
closer. Let’s get ready for the grand finale.

100
00:08:43,679 --> 00:08:44,559
Month 12

101
00:08:45,680 --> 00:08:51,051
Finally, at the end of the year,, the moon 
has reached the Roche limit. That’s the point  

102
00:08:51,051 --> 00:08:56,800
where Earth’s gravitational pull on the Moon is 
stronger than the Moon’s own gravity. Things on  

103
00:08:56,800 --> 00:09:02,320
the lunar surface start falling towards Earth 
and by the time it crosses 10,000 km the entire  

104
00:09:02,320 --> 00:09:07,840
moon disintegrates into rubble, smearing itself 
into a massive ring system around the earth.

105
00:09:08,640 --> 00:09:12,560
Fortunately, the moon’s disintegration 
means the misery on Earth has ended.  

106
00:09:13,360 --> 00:09:19,760
No moon means the general apocalyptic nature 
of things comes to a halt. The oceans recede,  

107
00:09:19,760 --> 00:09:21,840
flowing off the land one last time.

108
00:09:22,720 --> 00:09:28,240
Any survivors are treated to a view 
of tremendous arches spanning the sky,  

109
00:09:28,240 --> 00:09:32,640
glimmering in the sunlight, illuminating 
the night sky more brilliantly than any  

110
